Short:    AmiLines DELUXE (Another Logic Game)
Author:   Aleksandr Sinickin
Uploader: cbug@cch.pmc.ru (Misha Malyshev)
Type:     game

This is a small game out of a number of games that were made in Russia.
Remember TETRIS?  Well, this is something totally different but just as
addictive and logical.  You will see the coloured balls in your dreams!
Have sleepless nights and work spoiled ;-)

This is a must have!

Most of the game is in russian and the docs are too, so read info here!


SYSTEMS:
=======

Amiga with AGA chips, 2Mb Ram, HD.

RULES:
=====

Align sets of 5 or more same coloured balls in lines and score.
The bigger the lines the more you score!  It's just as simple.
Game ends when the field is full and you loose.

HISTORY:
=======

This is first public version and also v3.21

I have cleaned up the distribution archive and prepared it for upload.

Please note that there are  bugs in this version that we  know of,  so
please don't bombard us with mail.

If you decide  to make a clone  I can supply you with in-depth info on
how this game works.

